Easy Analogy

Imagine teaching a student.

📚 Give them millions of books to read.
✍️ Ask questions after every page.
❌ Correct mistakes.
🔁 Repeat this process millions of times.
🎓 Finally, teach them how to communicate politely and follow instructions.

That is broadly how ChatGPT is developed: first through large-scale pre-training on text, and then through additional training
to become a helpful conversational assistant.

============

In one sentence: ChatGPT did not suddenly appear in 2022—it is the result of years of research, beginning with the Transformer breakthrough in 2017, 
followed by successive GPT models, large-scale pre-training, and additional instruction-focused training to create a conversational AI.

